disableParam_NT.Wiki: Exclude from the NT version or mark the ones to be excluded.

disableParam_Product.Wiki: Exclude from the product version or mark the items to be excluded.

set00_beginCameraId.Wiki: Camera ID to play at start.

set00_endCameraId.Wiki: Camera ID to play at end.

set00_bNoWait.Wiki: Play now or wait for system wait time if not play.

set00_bFade.Wiki: Fade in and fade out according to the camera animation (if there is no animation, the system will process at a fixed time)

set00_bBoke.IsBool: Blur according to the camera animation (if there is no animation, process at a fixed system time)

set00_bOtherAnimCancel.Wiki: Do you want to cancel the end playback of this camera before starting playback?

set00_bFilterAnimOnly.Wiki: Only the screen effect animation and the camera animation refer only to the animation frame.

set00_bCameraHightFixed.Wiki: Even if the height of the viewpoint dummy poly is moved during animation, it will be the difference from the reference height.

set00_laneCamStartFrame.Wiki: Initial frame of lane camera animation when switching cameras.

set00_baseDmyPolyId.Wiki: Play the camera based on the specified dummy poly (i.e. playback position offset).

set00_laneCamLockAtEntityId.Wiki: If the lane camera viewpoint entity ID (value of the last two digits of 101700) is -1, it is the own aircraft.

set00_laneCamPointIdx.Wiki: Entity ID referenced by the lane camera point region (value of the last digit of 101600).

set00_laneCamLookAtDmyPolyId.AltName: Lane Camera: Viewpoint Dummy Polygon ID [0]
set00_laneCamLookAtDmyPolyId.Wiki: Damipoly ID from the lane camera viewpoint (if -1, damipoly 899 of your own aircraft's head part)
